\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 Virgil snapped his fingers: "I remember something about that. Found her in a cemetery, right? The Iowa guys covered it, out of Des Moines. Did she go to school here in Homestead?"\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 Laurie said, "Maybe, but her house would be out in the Northwest High area… I mean, some people transfer around depending on where their parents work. So, I don't know where she went."\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "Had she graduated, or was she working?" Virgil asked.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 Laurie said, "I don't know, really…"\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 A man two booths down from them cleared his throat and said, "She was homeschooled. She had a summer job here in Homestead, at the Dairy Queen. My daughter knew her."\par
