\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "That wouldn't be any women you know," Virgil said, "or have known, or will ever know."\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "Au contraire, my ignorant Minnewegan friend. My standing is well known in the female community. So, is this a social call?"\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "Nope. Something's wrong," Virgil said.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "Ah, crap," Wood said. Wood was the number two guy in the major crimes section. "Let's hear it."\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "You know the murder of a young Minnesota girl named Kelly Baker?" Virgil asked. "Down by Estherville, a year or so ago?"\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "That would be 'up by Estherville,' if you were correctly oriented. Yeah, I do know about it. Ugly. Ugly case, Virgil. October eleventh. Fourteen months ago. Our sex kitten. We got nothing."\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "You got sex kitten," Virgil said.\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "We do. Are you at your office? I'll send you the file."\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "Actually, I'm in Homestead…" He filled in Wood on the three murders, beginning with Flood. Wood listened, then said, "I heard about the jail hanging, but I didn't know it was murder."\par
\s0 \qj\snext0\f1\fs24\b0\i0\fi567\li0\ri0 "Just found it out today," Virgil said. "This morning. Listen, that file on Baker, shoot it down to me. Up to me."\par
